		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />And here we have another! I wonder how many people have been waiting for this one:
<br />
<br />Pocket Bomberman!
<br />
<br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/pocketbm.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/pocketbm.zip</a>
<br />
<br />What I do is I use No$Gmb to find the proper banks and addresses that I need, then I use a hex editor to extract the banks I need, then I add a bootstrap before $4000, then it usually works, but when it doesn't, I look over the code in the rom, and then see if I need to modify something. I don't actually debug the gbs itself. Mostly because I don't have anything to turn it into a rom.
<br />
<br />That usually is enough to get a working gbs, but I kinda break the rule of "clean it up!". <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />
<br />
<br />Edit (because I don't like replying to my own posts):
<br />Now, Krusty's Fun House
<br />
<br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/krusty.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/krusty.zip</a>
<br />
<br />Yeah, I know this has an NSF counterpart which sounds almost the same, but there are still some differences, and besides, the world needs more GBS files!
<br />
<br />edit 2:
<br />World Bowling
<br />
<br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/wbowling.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/wbowling.zip</a>
<br />
<br />Not a whole lot of songs though... then again, it's a bowling game.
